Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In October I gave change to a homeless guy (19 points). Last Tuesday I gave a wet willie, then I took it back (-5 points). In August I gave a kidney (1000 points). Last Thursday I helped across the street (6 points). Last Monday I invaded Iraq, broke it, and couldn't glue it back together before Mom got home (-1012 points).

Overall, I've been nice (8 points). For Christmas I deserve an XBox 360!

Sincerely,
electric_worry

- Take four books off your bookshelf. - Write the first sentence - Write the last sentence on page fifty - Write the second sentence on page one hundred - Write the next to the last sentence on page one hundred fifty - Write the final sentence of the book - Let your friends guess what book it is. BOOK ONE: - It was sunny in San Francisco; a fabulous condition. - If he could feel no guilt he could not fall into the trap of betraying fear or being caught. - As he entered his second term he was forty-one years old; Raymond's mother was thirty-eight. - Zilkov was proud of the power he represented. - "No electric chair for a medal of honor man," Marco said, and he began to pick his way painfully down the iron ladder listening intently for a memory of Raymond, for the faintest rustle of his ever having lived, but there was none. BOOK TWO: - GOOD EVENING - If this is not your natural milieu as a writer, however, there are still a few respectable magazines out there devoted to publishing short stories in the classic genres. - In Kansas City, a hobo declared himself Duke of All the West and began demanding tithes. - The next night, the mark and the pajama man will meet in front of the mark's office, or the mark's own home, or that of his aunts. - The politics of ancient Rome shall only serve as a backdrop for what is ultimately a personal story about a nervous, lame, antisocial man who escapes assassination to become the unlikely author of a book of fake trivia. BOOK THREE: - Solving the following riddle will reveal the awful secret behind the universe, assuming you do not go utterly mad in the attempt. - "I was asleep by two." - "I keep stuff down there." - I shook one out into my palm and stepped up to the door. - "Your ball." BOOK FOUR: - I still get nightmares. - Parallel surfaces will create a flutter echo, though frequently a splay of as little as 16mm (5/8 inch) can prevent the multiple repetitions. - FUCK. - I'm sorry Hailey. - "Whoever has no house now, will never have one."

I roleplay multiple characters from media I've never watched/read/played and have yet to be called on it. Fact: I have neither played Tales of the Abyss, watched Fate/Stay-Night, or read any Marvel Comics, yet have semi-active accounts for Legretta, Saber, and Deadpool. I admittedly only ever used Saber in, I dunno, one thread? But otherwise, I've skated by. I have broken each knee multiple times, and on one occasion, both at once. I broke my left knee tripping down the stairs when I was four, my right in a bike accident when I was 7, and both at 14 on a play at the plate. I still walk with a limp. If you're paying attention, you'll recall that this was the third statement. That's because the second... I own and am licensed to carry a Smith & Wesson 910. ...was the lie. It's a Beretta 98.
